<li id="cite_note-Cappelletty_.27.27et_al.27.27_.282005.29-33"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Cappelletty_.27.27et_al.27.27_.282005.29_33-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFCappelletty_G.2C_Brown_M.2C_Shumate_S2005">Cappelletty G, Brown M, Shumate S (2005). "Correlates of the Randolph Attachment Disorder Questionnaire (RADQ) in a Sample of Children in Foster Placement". <i>Child and Adolescent Social Work Journal</i> <b>22</b> (1): 71–84. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1007%2Fs10560-005-2556-2" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1007%2Fs10560-005-2556-2" rel="nofollow">10.1007/s10560-005-2556-2</a></span>.  "The findings showed that children in foster care have reported symptoms within the range typical of children not involved in foster care. The conclusion is that the RADQ has limited usefulness due to its lack of specificity with implications for treatment of children in foster care".</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Correlates+of+the+Randolph+Attachment+Disorder+Questionnaire+%28RADQ%29+in+a+Sample+of+Children+in+Foster+Placement&amp;rft.jtitle=Child+and+Adolescent+Social+Work+Journal&amp;rft.aulast=Cappelletty+G%2C+Brown+M%2C+Shumate+S&amp;rft.au=Cappelletty+G%2C+Brown+M%2C+Shumate+S&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.volume=22&amp;rft.issue=1&amp;rft.pages=71%E2%80%9384&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1007%2Fs10560-005-2556-2&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Reactive_attachment_disorder"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
